By: Muhammad
Glossary:
  - Term: Shahâdah
    Definition: A central formula of  Islâm. theurgic in essence,
      and hence really untranslatable. It is roughly translated as,
      'There is no divinity if not the Divinity.'
Commentary: A key text of the Shahâdah
---
Those who repeat： Là ilâha illâ 'llâh, will not experience solitude
at the moment of death, nor on the Day of Resurrection.
